The paper presents a new distributed representation in deep neural nets, which is a fundamental topic in machine learning. The paper discusses various applications such as handwritten digits recognition, face reconstruction, sequence to sequence learning, EEG classification, and graph-based node classification, which are related to computer vision, natural language processing, and neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
